    </div>

    <!-- IMMEDIATE VS EXTENDED -->
    <h2 id="release-types">Immediate vs Extended Release: Which Adults Need Which?</h2>

    <p>The release mechanism of a melatonin gummy is more clinically meaningful than the milligram number on the label, because it determines whether the supplement matches your specific sleep problem. Mismatching release type to sleep type is one of the most common reasons adults report that "melatonin doesn't work" — the molecule is fine; the mechanism was wrong for the issue.</p>

    <div class="vs-strip">
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Immediate-Release Melatonin</strong>
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Sleep onset insomnia (trouble falling asleep). <strong>Mechanism:</strong> Raises blood melatonin within 20-40 minutes; cleared in 4-5 hours. <strong>Adult use case:</strong> Younger adults whose sleep problem is falling asleep, not staying asleep. Most over-the-counter gummies are this type. Take 30-60 minutes before target bedtime.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Extended-Release Melatonin</strong>
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Sleep maintenance insomnia (waking during the night). <strong>Mechanism:</strong> Sustained release over 6-8 hours. <strong>Adult use case:</strong> Adults over 50, perimenopausal and menopausal individuals, and anyone who falls asleep fine but wakes at 3-4 AM. Less common in gummy format; check the supplement facts panel for "extended" or "dual phase" wording.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Dual-Release (Bi-Layer)</strong>
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Adults with both sleep onset and maintenance issues. <strong>Mechanism:</strong> Initial pulse followed by sustained release. <strong>Adult use case:</strong> Comprehensive sleep architecture support; useful for adults over 50 with multifactorial sleep complaints. Newer technology — fewer gummy options exist.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Combination Formulas</strong>
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Adults who want lower melatonin paired with botanical support. <strong>Mechanism:</strong> Lower melatonin (1-3mg) combined with L-theanine, magnesium, chamomile, or passionflower. <strong>Adult use case:</strong> Anxiety-driven insomnia, melatonin-sensitive adults, or people who want to taper down from high-dose melatonin alone.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="warn-box">
      <span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span>
      <p><strong>Most gummy labels do not specify release type clearly.</strong> If the supplement facts panel does not say "immediate" or "extended," assume immediate-release. Adults primarily experiencing 3 AM awakenings should specifically seek out products labeled "extended-release," "sustained release," or "dual-phase," or consider non-gummy formats where extended-release is more standardized.</p>
    </div>

